This paper deals with Knowledge Base Population (KBP) tasks, which involve natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract structured information from unstructured text. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves supervised and unsupervised learning methods, which are common in cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge bases, which are typically stored in databases, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category as well.
